http://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2013/07/19/pm-opens-mugda-hospital PM opens Mugda hospital], ''[[Bdnews24.com]]''</ref>\n\nThis hospital is home to a new medical college of Bangladesh. It is the 4th government medical college inside Dhaka metropolitan city. From the first month of 2016, it has started classes of regular MBBS course.<ref>{{cite news |date=1 April 2014 |title=Mugda General Hospital to get medical college by Jan: Nasim |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/mugda-general-hospital-to-get-medical-college-by-jan-nasim-18221 |newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref>\n\nThis medical college is running their 5th batch already. It has its own cultural, sports and social committee. Different programmes are held on occasions.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of medical colleges in Bangladesh]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Public Medical Colleges of Bangladesh}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Medical colleges in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Dhaka]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in Dhaka]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2015]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in Bangladesh]]\n\n\n{{Bangladesh-edu-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Orphan|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| name        = Mugda Medical College & Hospital \n| org/group   = \n| logo        = \n| logo_size   = \n| image       = \n| image_size  = 225 \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| latitude    = \n| longitude   = \n| coordinates = {{Coord|23.7324|N|90.4302|E|region:BD_type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n| location    = Mugdapara, [[Dhaka]]\n| region      = \n| state       = \n| country     = [[Bangladesh]]\n| healthcare  = <!-- UK: NHS; AU/CA: Medicare; ELSE free-form text, e.g. Private -->\n| funding     = \n| type        =  [[Hospital]] and [[Public university|Public]] [[medical school]]\n| affiliation = \n| patron      = \n| network     = \n| standards   = \n| emergency   = \n| helipad     = \n| beds        = 500\n| speciality